text: Audubon County is a county in the U.S. state of Iowa. As of the 2020 census, the population was 5,674, making it Iowa's third-least populous county. The county seat is Audubon. The county was founded on January 15, 1851 and named after John James Audubon, the naturalist and artist. == References == Category:1851 establishments in Iowa Category:Iowa counties
title: Audubon County, Iowa
